H1> Granting admin access

P> Administrators are regular users with elevated permissions. Each admin can be granted exactly the permissions they need – nothing more – so day-to-day moderators never see the dangerous areas of the site.

SHOT> administrators/admin-users.png | Permission matrix when editing an administrator

Q> What are permissions?
A> Permissions allow you to give administrators different access levels to the admin section. For example you might only want to let a certain admin post news items; using permissions you can do that. There are some admin functions that are only accessible to the [b]main site admin[/b] for security reasons.

WARN> The main site admin (user #1) cannot have its permissions revoked – this is by design so the site can never be locked out of itself.

H1> Promoting an existing member

STEP> Open [b]Admin → Users[/b] and search for the registered member.
STEP> Click [b]Make Admin[/b] in the row actions.
STEP> Go immediately to the [b]Administrators[/b] section.
STEP> Tick the permissions the new admin should have and save.

TIP> The same workflow lets you [b]revoke[/b] admin status: just clear the permissions or click [b]Remove Admin[/b].
